        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=41204&TOPIC_ID=5436&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=an+interesting+thread+from+the+FOH+board&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Couldn't help but post this one:</P><P><BR>"Here lies the greatest complaint with the Necro class. </P><P>Unlike all other classes, it's role changes from offensive to utility 50+. By level 20 in all classes you have a very good idea what you are in for. No matter the situation. </P><P>Prior to 50 a necro brings to a group a variety of tools which are indeed useful, including devastating DOTs and decent nukes. Also a very stupid but powerful pet. </P><P>However, after 44 the necro doesn't receive a nuke upgrade until 57. And then it's simply a spell which does twice the damage, for twice the mana, for twice the time. No different than casting the previous nuke twice. </P><P>Also, many of the necros capabilities are dependent on being able to lifetap. Creating mobs which prevent lifetapping shut down the class. </P><P>Then there is the fact of dot stacking. No more than 2 necros can be on the offensive on a raid. Also, do to aggro management, every time a tick rolls around the necro gets summoned with many of our dots. Nukers get summoned for over nuking. Necros get summoned just because of one dot. </P><P>So, 50+ for effeciency sake, the necro just sends his pet and sits down. Should any "useful" caster die or be oom, then the necro feeds him. </P><P>Prior to Kunark, there was a coalition of necros known as the NDS - necro death squad. </P><P>5 50 necro's and a 50 cleric broke fear. Due to the abundance of undead charmable mobs mainly, and players with gonads. </P><P>Now, however, we have the NPS - necro pump squad. 5 necros and a bard with mana song. </P><P>It's very frustrating to play the only caster class which says High difficulty only to discover your reward for all the punishment you take is to give others your mana at a 35% efficiency. </P><P>Necros are: <BR>- the only class requiring the farming of reagents (bone chips) <BR>- the only class who has 3 vendors in game with reagents (coffins are found in Neriak, Cabilis, and Sky) <BR>- the class with the most expensive reagents (coffin 150pp, tiny coffin 75pp, essence emerald 1k) <BR>- the only class who has time of day restrictions on spells (example is a form of 18 sec invulnerability which only works at night) <BR>- the only pet class that requires an extra reagent for pet but gets nothing special about pet (59 pet requires peridot, is the same as 49 pet with 200 extra hps & possibly 4 levels higher) <BR>- does not get an unfearable pet <BR>- does not get a sow'd pet <BR>- does not get COTH for pet (told this is coming however) <BR>- does not get a damage shield for pet <BR>- does not get a pet with any kind of resistances <BR>- Loses ability to keep 53 and 56 pets alive <BR>- does not get a haste item for pet (although one from magician works fine) <BR>- Pays a total of 650 mana to summon pet versus 400 that magician pays <BR>- does not get a focus quest for pre 49 pets <BR>- does not get a summon weapon for pets needing them (pre 39) <BR>- gets one buff people want but which cannot be used in various zones (kedge, sky, hole) <BR>- is the master of the undead, yet always behind the cleric in killing undead <BR>- is transformed into a utility class which caps out at 35% efficiency (unlike rez, mez, slow, haste) <BR>- does not get an upgraded feign death (unlike hybrid class) <BR>- does not get upgrade to summon corpse prior to hybrid class obtaining it </P><P><BR>Basically, the only times I've EVER been invited to a raid based on NEED is Sky which requires summon corpse to complete. Or a Trak raid to DMF. </P><P>But even then all I did was sit and wait for <BR>/ooc a_cleric_01 OOM <BR>/ooc a_chanter_02 OOM <BR>/ooc a_shaman_03 OOM </P><P>And then twitch them. </P><P>Oh, and I forgot </P><P>- Get the most UBER epic of all with a 49 spell on it</P><P>~Neekorpolis"</P><P>I am your Uber torch<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

